Concepts Used
Classical Mechanics
Lagrangian dynamics
Torque and force balance
Control Theory
PID control
State-space representation
LQR optimal control
Numerical Methods
ODE solving (Runge-Kutta)
Small angle linearization
Nonlinear Dynamics
Underactuated systems
Stability analysis


Logic Flow
Initialize system parameters (masses, lengths)
Set up control system (PID/LQR)

Simulate dynamics:
Compute forces and torques
Integrate equations of motion

Animate:
Draw cart and pendulum
Update in real-time


Pseudocode
text
1. Set parameters: M, m, l, g, b, c
2. Initialize state: x, θ, dx, dθ = 0
3. For each timestep:
   a. Compute control force F (PID/LQR)
   b. Calculate accelerations:
      - Solve coupled ODEs for ddx and ddθ
   c. Update state (Euler/RK4 integration)
   d. Draw:
      - Cart (rectangle)
      - Pendulum (line + bob)
      - Force arrow
4. Repeat for animation
